      "rendered": "<p>An Instagram Photo and Video Essay by Heather Mansfield For many years I&#8217;ve wanted to visit The Hague, Netherlands. ??\u00a0Known as the International City of Peace and Justice, there are more than 160 NGOs in Den Haag\u00a0working to make the world a better place. I was in the Netherlands for the International Fundraising Congress\u00a0(on behalf of OnGood.ngo) and without a scheduled agenda and only the hope of meeting\u00a0some\u00a0NGOs staff, I took the train down from Amsterdam and wandered the streets with a smartphone in hand and an international data plan. The first nonprofit spotted on my #HagueDayTrip was the Mauritshuis\u00a0 </p>\n",
